I’m working on auto and I’m having problems with rotations, whenever the robot rotates it loses zero I don’t know what I’m doing wrong in the code. Could someone please take a look at my code and give me some suggestions. the sooner the better for we are leaving for competition today.
Thanks,
Sam Gross,
Team 2654

  • When you say it loses its zero are you saying that the gyro 0 position is changing? i.e. when you push the joystick forward that direction is changing when you rotate.
  • I see you have ~8 autos, does this happen with every auton or just a particular one?
  • I see in your drivebase code you have a NavX but in robot container & your autons you use a pigeon. Just want to confirm you’re not using the NavX?
  • Does the robot drive normally in teleop and only have this heading issue when you run auton?

so in the first auto we tell it to go to zero, and if we don’t rotate it, it goes to zero, but when we rotate it it just goes forward towards the front of the robot instead of rotating the robot back and moving to the original position.

It happens on every auto.

Yes we are using NavX, but we are also using the pigeon

yes it drives normally in Teleop.
